                <note rend="inline" type="source">551.5F1/38: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-28T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 28, 1931—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. Embassy’s 49, February 20, 4 p.m. You will acknowledge to Mr. MacDonald the
                    receipt of his communication relative to an international conference on silver.
                    Tell him that we are giving the matter consideration and especially his more
                    comprehensive plan to handle the situation. It should be made clear to the Prime
                    Minister that, owing to the pressure of business attending the adjournment of
                    Congress, we cannot reply immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
